2SER FM radio Interview with Shri Mataji, Sydney (Australia) May 6th, 1987

Question: What is Sahaja yoga?

Shri Mataji: 'Sahaja-'saha means 'with',a means 'born'.Born with you is Sahaja. Yoga means union with the divine., that is 'spontaneous union with the divine.'

Question: And is it for all ages?

Shri Mataji: Yes. For all ages, for everyone. It is an evolutionary process which ends up with your ultimate goal and that is, to become the Spirit. And so it is meant for everyone.

Question: And how does it differ from other forms of yoga?

Shri Mataji: Other forms of yogas are leading to this one so that you are purified to receive this spontaneous yoga. But there is no need to do anywhere or do anything for this. You can get your realisation without doing anything, any one of them.

Question: What is Self-realization?

Shri Mataji: Self-realisation is that, so far the Spirit, which is in your heart, which is witnessing your activities, but does not come into play, into your actions nor into your intelligence, nor into your attention. But once you get Self-realized then the Spirit, the light of the Spirit shines and that's how your whole attitude towards life changes. You become a transformed personality.

Question: Are you the only person that can give Self-realisation?

Shri Mataji: No. There are many Sahaja yogis who can give Self-realisation to many people.

Question: Shri Mataji, the publicity I read you can actually give Self-realisation en masse?

Shri Mataji: Yes.

Question: Why is it possible?

Shri Mataji: The time has come for giving en masse realisation I think and I am making the best of it.

Question is: And in what way does one's life change one's health after self-realisation?

Shri Mataji: A Sahaja yogi is a person whose guideline is his spirit. Thus he is standing at a point which is Absolute. He is not relatively looking after his life. He is on an Absolute point means whatever he does is the absolute truth. He doesn't take to anything that is an untruth which is false, which is superficial. That is how he is absolutely tranquil and peaceful and dynamic. And he has all the qualities of a very good gentleman like he is righteous, he is very pure and also he is very virtuous. We need people of that kind today, to make a new world.

Question: Do you think the world is in a very precarious situation?

Shri Mataji: It is.Very much. You can see all around. It is in a very precarious way placed and this is the time when one starts thinking of something better or to get out of it and that is the time it works out the best.

Question: What are the other countries is there, Sahaja yoga?

Shri Mataji: There is a big list. There are about fourteen to fifteen countries involved in Sahaja yoga. To name them, we can say, in U.K, France, Spain, Austria, Australia, of course, is first. Then we have on the other side Switzerland, Germany. What else, America.About fifteen countries altogether.Algeria.

Question: Why are you called the Mother?

Shri Mataji: 'Mother'.Because I gave them the second birth(.laughs)

Question: That is a very simple answer.

Shri Mataji:(laughs) That is the answer. The one who gives you birth is the mother, isn't? That's how they call me the Mother. But also the mother's qualities are needed today. The patience, the love, the compassion, the understanding and also commanding the confidence of all the children, is only in a mother. That is why it is better to be a mother.

Question: How difficult do you think is to live a life once you become involved in Sahaja yoga?

Shree Mataji: It is the easiest life to lead because you then come across people who are very good. They are of the same type, a good rapport is there. Very great friendship, a big fraternity. And also you find life much more interesting that you don't think about them but you enjoy everything. So life is much easier after Realisation. You are dynamic. Your problems get solved. Your health improves. So in every way, it is such a great blessing.

Question: I don't have any more questions but is there anything else you would like to add?

Shri Mataji: Yes. That now we are standing at a point where the evolution has reached us to human awareness and that is not absolute. We have to jump to higher awareness and that is the last Spirit and that one has to be achieved by everyone. Otherwise, there is no solution to all kinds of problems people are facing today.

Thank you.

