Shri Mataji: No, you know, if the media wants, actually it is en masse and also there was never a media like this. If the wants they can help the whole world. Isn't it? They have to give the truth to the people, but if they do not want to do it then they are the ones who are held responsible.

Person: The media is divided into two parts.One who gives real truthful accounts and the other which does not.

Shri Mataji: Another thing is also that you see when they become sort of doubtful about it, they say first give us the Realization and then we will do it, which is very difficult. Sometimes you can't give them. It is being very selfish but I can't give Realization to someone, doesn't mean there isn't anything like that. But in Italy, when I went there, there was a fellow called Ramano. He was a big fan of people and a very interesting person. He said, Mother, I must ask you one thing. I said what? Please give me a Realization. I said I have to broadcast. Mother first give me Realisation. It will be a good idea. Then I gave him Realization. Then he laughed and laughed. The joke is over. The joke is over. (Shri Mataji laughs) What about our program? He said, No, no, we will have the program. Then we went to a place and then he said these people are monkeys. They cannot understand Sahaja yoga. I said,' Why?' He said they won't understand any Sahaja yoga, Mother. You just don't talk to them. Then he gave me big publicity in Milano. Then we went to a hill station. There we gathered about six to seven hundred people there and gave me such big publicity, the Romano fellow. Wonderful person.

One person in the room: It is very different this time Mother. Last time, your last visit the people in the press wanted something sensational, they wanted something clever, a big trick. This time the same people are not interested. This time the people who are showing interest are receptive to the message. It's quite remarkable. Same thing happening in Melbourne too. All the sensationalist are not interested. So hope we get very good coverage.

Shri Mataji: This sensation business also comes from materialism I think. Human beings are becoming matter. So they need some sensations to come up to something. They cannot see something which is very obvious and good for them. They need some sensations. Like this gentleman asked me, we have to go outside on the street. I said street it won't work out because it is quite a serious subject. How can I discuss with you on the street? He compromised for the garden and we went to the garden and all the cloud started pouring there. Then he said that is over and we start the whole thing and it started raining and afterwards he gave up.

Another person: Started raining just when we were trying to give him Realization. Heavens were warning us.

Shri Mataji: You see, there are people who are thinking, who are worried, who want to do something great. But we have to approach them somehow. The approach has to be built up. Once that is built up there is no problem. That is the main thing. The right type of people we should meet. Like the first time whether n I went to Italy, we had informed the newspaper to advertise and I stayed in a hotel. One girl was with  me.No body contacted us.No body came in the hall. Not even a single soul. Nothing was done. Nothing worked out. So we went back spending so much of money. And now in Italy, can you imagine, at the airport, if you go, the whole airport is full of Sahajayogies. It happens like that. Same with our  Calcutta. First time when I went to Calcutta there was one person in the hall. And this time when I went there the biggest hall they have, was given to us and the crowd was so much and they were saying' Ma, ma' and nobody could come inside because the hall was full. Thousands and thousands were waiting outside. And now it has taken such a form, even the cinema actors went there to collect money for our school in Calcutta. You can't believe the same Calcutta where there was only one single soul in the big hall and I thought this fellow will also run away after five minutes(laughs). It does change gradually. But one should not be shocked with the first appearance.

